Hi Derek,

Here is the network XML format currently generated by SharpNEAT. Spot 
the difference :)

&lt;network&gt;
  &lt;neurons&gt;
    &lt;neuron id=&quot;0&quot; type=&quot;bias&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;neuron id=&quot;1&quot; type=&quot;in&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;neuron id=&quot;3&quot; type=&quot;out&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;neuron id=&quot;215&quot; type=&quot;hid&quot; /&gt;
  &lt;/neurons&gt;
  &lt;connections&gt;
    &lt;connection src-id=&quot;0&quot; tgt-id=&quot;3&quot; weight=&quot;-2.19017208287113&quot; /&gt;
  &lt;/connections&gt;
&lt;/network&gt;

I can change in/out to input/output. Although I prefer the shorthand 
version I&#39;m not /that/ bothered + it&#39;s a trivial change for me to do. If 
anyone else is going to want to try and generate SVG it looks like you 
will also currently have to change the &quot;bias&quot; to be an &quot;input&quot; and add 
your own hint-* attributes and a  [recurrent=&quot;false&quot;] attribute on each 
conenction. I&#39;ll look into optionally outputting this extra stuff from 
SharpNEAT and perhaps tying in an SVG viewer of some sort.

Colin.
